      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start with the stats. For the next part of the outline, I want to address the counter-arguments. A lot of people argue that meritocracy is the fair way to do things and that people should just be rewarded based on their hard work. How should I frame that opposing view in my paper so it doesn't undermine my main argument? Like, how do I show that those views are basically just ignoring the systemic stuff?",
