      "content": "You can frame the meritocracy argument as a naive, individualistic perspective that ignores the structural barriers that prevent people of color from achieving economic mobility. By attributing poverty and inequality to individual failures, rather than acknowledging the role of systemic racism and privilege, proponents of meritocracy are effectively excusing the continued exploitation of marginalized communities. This ignores the fact that people of color are often forced to navigate a biased education system, discriminatory hiring practices, and limited access to capital and networks, all of which hinder their ability to achieve economic success through hard work alone.",
